headlines.description: — Kelly Olynyk scored 25 points and the short-handed Utah Jazz beat Detroit 119-111 on Thursday night for the Pistons' 25th straight loss — one short of the NBA single season record.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons drop 25th straight to move within loss of tying NBA single-season record

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Trey Murphy III scored 28 points while starting in place of New Orleans star Zion Williamson — out with an illness — and the Pelicans pulled away in the second half to beat the undermanned Cleveland Cavaliers 123-104 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trey Murphy III scores 28 points while filling in for Zion as Pelicans beat Cavaliers 123-104

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 20 points and eight assists in his first home game following a 25-game suspension to help the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Indiana Pacers 116-103 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ja Morant has 20 points in first home game following suspension, Grizzlies beat Pacers 116-103

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 32 points and the Washington Wizards held off the Portland Trail Blazers 118-117 on Thursday night for their fifth victory of the season.
